article.headline: EIA reports a 93 billion cubic foot weekly climb in U.S. natural-gas supplies
article.body: The U.S. Energy Information Administration reported Thursday that domestic supplies of natural gas rose by 93 billion cubic feet for the week ended June 5. That was slightly less than the average increase of 95 billion forecast by analysts polled by S&P Global Platts. Total stocks now stand at 2.807 trillion cubic feet, up 748 billion cubic feet from a year ago, and 421 billion cubic feet above the five-year average, the government said. July natural gas ngn20 was up 2.8 cents, or 1.6%, at $1.808 per million British thermal units. It was trading at $1.813 before the data.
